result.name: Coffee Break

reviews.text:
Great for spare ribs!
A true gem in the middle of the market.

We were looking for a place to eat with the two kids and were afraid to try things we didn't know in the market. Given that we are westerners, we were also afraid to get stomach pains or worse.

The food was really good and the staff friendly. The Golden dish for me was the spare ribs and the pumpkin soup. Definitely a level above the rest. I recommend you don't leave HK without trying it.
Great value for money , try the mega burger, only 88 dollars. Good craft beers also. Only negative is only accept cash payments.
Good place to chill and chat with mates in this busy part of town, generally not to busy in the afternoon and gives a cozy vibe.
Fair priced, good environment, quality food, big portion
Great food, great coffee. Also features some board games id you wanna spend some time with friends and relatives. The only caveat is the restaurant sets a limit on dining time.

result.formatted_address: 2 Tung Choi Street (Ladies' Market), Mong Kok, 香港
result.name: Coffee Break

reviews.text:
鵝肝牛肉漢堡超讚😍😍😍🍔🍔🍔
服務也很貼心😆😆😆
1:00有set lunch食，加$2, 30元就有杯特式咖啡價位可接受的。室內面積不算大，所以同隔離枱都幾近，所以坐滿人都真係幾嘈!是次點咗個pizza,好味嘅但略過火，邊位硬咗d及燶。咖啡味夠淡。不過位置喺正女人街入便行到熱辣辣入嚟過下冷河亦唔錯。繁忙時間限時90分鐘。

鮮茄蓉大蝦燴意大利飯，加南瓜湯和凍摩卡，盛惠130元，CP值算不錯。
意大利飯有點過硬，飯中加了大量菇粒，增加口感。蕃茄汁有點太酸，大蝦雖然煎香的，但不新鮮。
南瓜湯很濃郁，很滿意。
鵝肝漢堡又大又好食一個人差d食唔哂 大蝦意大利粉咸左小小但都唔錯
d野好食，不過要有耐性因為廚房細多客時出菜慢。
